00:38:19,965 --> 00:38:22,532
"It stopped his breath."

557
00:38:22,534 --> 00:38:24,501
"Blue they were..."
Cut the marine life.

558
00:38:24,503 --> 00:38:25,502
"A blue beyond blue,
like the ocean."
Cliche.

559
00:38:26,537 --> 00:38:27,971
"A blue beyond blue
like..."

560
00:38:27,973 --> 00:38:30,440
Like nothing but blue.

561
00:38:30,442 --> 00:38:32,575
"A blue he could
swim into forever
and never miss..."

562
00:38:32,577 --> 00:38:33,777
Mmm, cut this.

563
00:38:33,779 --> 00:38:35,879
Then pick up with...

564
00:38:35,881 --> 00:38:38,515
Had there ever
been such blue? Had there
ever been such eyes?

565
00:38:38,517 --> 00:38:39,749
Don't need the rhetorical.

566
00:38:39,751 --> 00:38:41,384
Why?

567
00:38:41,386 --> 00:38:42,052
It's not a lightning bolt,
it's a digression.

568
00:38:43,754 --> 00:38:45,555
"A blue beyond..." No!

569
00:38:47,625 --> 00:38:48,591
Her eyes were blue.

570
00:38:49,327 --> 00:38:50,694
Better.

571
00:38:50,696 --> 00:38:51,995
And cut.

572
00:38:51,997 --> 00:38:54,964
He was worthless,
she was everything.

573
00:38:54,966 --> 00:38:58,735
She was a girl
across a room.
That's enough.

574
00:38:58,737 --> 00:39:02,672
And so, cut "the lost,
wandering souls..."

575
00:39:03,574 --> 00:39:05,075
Cut.

576
00:39:05,077 --> 00:39:07,711
"So quickly did
he fall for her

577
00:39:07,713 --> 00:39:10,447
"that no one in the room
even heard the sound,

578
00:39:10,449 --> 00:39:12,682
"the whoosh as he fell,
the clatter..."

579
00:39:12,684 --> 00:39:14,818
The whoosh, the clatter.
Is that the point?

580
00:39:14,820 --> 00:39:16,586
Well, what did you hear
when you fell in love?

581
00:39:16,588 --> 00:39:18,988
What did you hear?
Clattering?

582
00:39:18,990 --> 00:39:22,859
The point is it was all
happening inside him.

583
00:39:22,861 --> 00:39:25,995
His life changed,
no one else in the room
noticed anything.

584
00:39:25,997 --> 00:39:27,364
Then make that
the point.

585
00:39:27,366 --> 00:39:28,965
I hate to see
the words go!

586
00:39:30,134 --> 00:39:33,470
Maybe the larger
question is this.

587
00:39:33,472 --> 00:39:35,939
In a book crowded
with great rolling
mountains of prose,

588
00:39:35,941 --> 00:39:37,774
how is this moment
profoundly different?

589
00:39:39,410 --> 00:39:41,911
Because it's simple.
Unadorned.

590
00:39:41,913 --> 00:39:43,713
Like lightning.

591
00:39:43,715 --> 00:39:47,650
Standing out
in the black sky
by its starkness.

592
00:39:47,652 --> 00:39:48,585
Exactly.

593
00:39:52,022 --> 00:39:53,056
God damn!

594
00:39:59,497 --> 00:40:01,097
<i> All aboard!</i>

