1233
01:25:45,874 --> 01:25:47,141
Why not, tom?

1234
01:25:49,378 --> 01:25:51,545
I know he's your friend,
but you have no idea.

1235
01:25:52,547 --> 01:25:54,281
He crippled me.

1236
01:25:54,283 --> 01:25:55,916
He deformed my work.

1237
01:25:55,918 --> 01:25:58,218
He as much admitted it.

1238
01:25:58,220 --> 01:26:00,721
And then he tried
to take all the credit
for my success.

1239
01:26:00,723 --> 01:26:02,723
He did no such thing.
Do you know how
much you hurt him?

1240
01:26:02,725 --> 01:26:04,725
We hurt each other.

1241
01:26:04,727 --> 01:26:06,193
Don't be glib
with me, tom.

1242
01:26:06,195 --> 01:26:08,362
You don't know
what he did to me.

1243
01:26:08,364 --> 01:26:10,697
What he did to you?
Uh-huh.

1244
01:26:10,699 --> 01:26:12,733
What did he do?
He made all your
dreams come true.

1245
01:26:12,735 --> 01:26:15,169
He gave you a career.
A life!

1246
01:26:15,171 --> 01:26:18,272
There.
The scribner party line.
I expected more from you.

1247
01:26:18,274 --> 01:26:21,708
That decent man
believed in you
when nobody else would.

1248
01:26:21,710 --> 01:26:24,478
He poured all his hopes
and dreams into you.

1249
01:26:24,480 --> 01:26:28,348
All the things he would
never do, all the books
he would never write.

1250
01:26:28,350 --> 01:26:30,751
And now you repay him
with ugly accusations
and brutality.

1251
01:26:30,753 --> 01:26:31,885
You ought to be
ashamed of yourself!

1252
01:26:35,190 --> 01:26:37,324
That man has a genius
for friendship

1253
01:26:37,326 --> 01:26:40,360
and you've squandered it.

1254
01:26:40,362 --> 01:26:43,530
There will come a day
when you're not
the success you are now.

1255
01:26:43,532 --> 01:26:46,934
It's a long road
then, believe me.

1256
01:26:46,936 --> 01:26:49,503
Why hurt the one man
who will walk on
that road with you?

1257
01:27:05,486 --> 01:27:07,321
Daddy?

1258
01:27:07,323 --> 01:27:08,855
Hello, puppet.

1259
01:27:08,857 --> 01:27:11,291
Why doesn't tom
come around anymore?

1260
01:27:15,697 --> 01:27:16,630
Oh, Nancy.

1261
01:27:18,900 --> 01:27:20,767
Tom needs some
time for himself.

1262
01:27:21,569 --> 01:27:22,903
Is he coming back?

1263
01:27:24,239 --> 01:27:26,773
I don't think so.

1264
01:27:26,775 --> 01:27:30,577
See, tom's the kind of
fellow who needs to make
his own way through life.

1265
01:27:30,579 --> 01:27:32,246
Is he mad at us?
No, honey.

1266
01:27:33,715 --> 01:27:35,382
No, sometimes
people just go away.

1267
01:27:37,485 --> 01:27:40,387
They have to grow up,
leave home.

1268
01:27:40,389 --> 01:27:41,922
It'll happen
to you, too.

1269
01:27:41,924 --> 01:27:43,657
Poor daddy.
I miss him, too.

1270
01:27:50,298 --> 01:27:51,798
Tell you what,
get me his book.

1271
01:28:04,012 --> 01:28:06,847
"A destiny that leads
the English to the Dutch
is strange enough

1272
01:28:09,384 --> 01:28:12,452
